    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MICROSOFT ABANDONS JOINT CONTROL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Microsoft Corp, European Union concerns, changes its accord to acquire 23.7 percent of Telewest Communications PLC so that it will have on control over management of British cable television company (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>After raising concern among regulators in Europe, the Microsoft Corporation changed its agreement to acquire 23.7 percent of Telewest Communications P.L.C. so that it would have no control over the management of Britain's second-largest cable television company. The European Union had objected to Microsoft's initial deal with Telewest because of the software company's possible dominance of television set-top box software in Britain.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
